## Privacy disclosure

Per the platform's privacy policy:

- **Owner-visible bundles** include every `events[].payload`, the
  scratchpad body (if any), and the final diff verbatim.
- **Share-token bundles** ship payloads only for a closed safe-list
  of event types whose shape is structurally PII-free (ids, booleans,
  counts, small enum strings — e.g. `session.started`,
  `patch.applied`, `test.run`). Every other event's payload —
  including `prompt.submitted`, `agent.responded`, `command.run`,
  and `validator.flag` — collapses to
  `{"redacted": true, "byte_count": N}`. The scratchpad body is
  omitted entirely, the seeded `agent_patch.diff` is omitted, and a
  newly-introduced event type is redacted by default until an
  operator audits its payload shape. The envelope, score report,
  event metadata, and final diff are unchanged.
- The score is generated by a deterministic Python grader. No LLM
  participates in scoring, ranking, or signing. AWS Bedrock-hosted
  Claude is used only for cached coaching prose (see the operator's
  privacy page); the cached bytes downstream signatures hash against
  are produced once and reused — the LLM is never on the hot path of
  any signed artefact.

